1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:08,000
Coding agents are everywhere, but comparing them is messy. Each demo uses different tools, prompts, and traces.

2
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:18,000
OpenCode Harness gives coding agents a shared runtime: one agent loop, one tool layer, one trace format, and one eval surface.

3
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:34,000
Run the same workflow across DeepSeek, Qwen, Claude, OpenAI, vLLM, SGLang, Ollama, and local endpoints.

4
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:50,000
The harness includes permissioned tools and MCP-compatible extension points for tools, resources, prompts, diagnostics, and approvals.

5
00:00:50,000 --> 00:01:04,000
Every run produces JSONL traces, provider transcripts, replay summaries, HTML reports, a terminal trace viewer, and an eval dashboard.

6
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:15,000
OpenCode Harness v0.1.0 is open source now. Use it to test, compare, and debug coding agents across model providers.
